Common Docker commands (concise reference)

- `docker --version`: show Docker version.
- `docker pull <image>`: download image from registry.
- `docker build -t <name>:<tag> .`: build image from Dockerfile.
- `docker images`: list local images.
- `docker run -it --rm -p <host>:<container> <image>`: run container interactively and remove on exit.
- `docker ps`: list running containers.
- `docker ps -a`: list all containers (including stopped).
- `docker stop <container>`: stop a running container.
- `docker rm <container>`: remove a stopped container.
- `docker logs <container>`: show container logs.
- `docker exec -it <container> <cmd>`: run a command inside a running container.
- `docker rmi <image>`: remove a local image.
- `docker system prune -a`: clean unused images, containers, networks (use with caution).
- `docker-compose up -d`: start services defined in `docker-compose.yml` (detached).
- `docker-compose down`: stop and remove compose services.

Tip: prefer small, single-purpose images and pin image tags for reproducibility.

